The United States is congratulating the Venezuelan people for participating in the recent presidential elections in a peaceful manner. They are calling on the Venezuelan government to respect the rights of citizens to peaceful assembly and free speech. The US is urging everyone to avoid violence and actions that could increase tensions. They also support an audit of the ballots and a credible and transparent process to reassure the Venezuelan people about the election results. This would contribute to political dialogue and the advancement of democracy in the country.